---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Magic — Illusion Terms That Score Big"
  description="Magic and illusion terms valid in Scrabble with full scoring. WIZARD (19pts), CONJURE (16pts), HEXING (17pts). Magic vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble magic words, wizard scrabble points, conjure scrabble, hexing scrabble word, magic vocabulary scrabble, illusion words scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Magic — Illusion Terms That Score Big","description":"Magic and illusion terms valid in Scrabble with full scoring. WIZARD (19pts), CONJURE (16pts), HEXING (17pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-magic"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is WIZARD a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! WIZARD scores 19 points (W=4, I=1, Z=10, A=1, R=1, D=2). The Z=10 and W=4 tiles combine for serious scoring power. Valid in both TWL and SOWPODS."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can you play CONJURE in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. CONJURE scores 16 points (C=3, O=1, N=1, J=8, U=1, R=1, E=1) as a 7-letter word. The J=8 provides most of the value, and at 7 letters it qualifies for the 50-point bingo bonus."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is HEXING valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! HEXING scores 17 points (H=4, E=1, X=8, I=1, N=1, G=2). The X=8 and H=4 tiles deliver excellent scoring from just 6 letters."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Magic — Illusion Terms That Score Big</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Magic vocabulary is spellbinding on the Scrabble board. WIZARD conjures 19 points with its Z=10 and W=4 combination, CONJURE channels J=8 for 16 points with bingo potential, and HEXING casts X=8 for 17 points in just 6 tiles. These words will make your score disappear — into the stratosphere.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">19 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">WIZARD (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">17 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">HEXING</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">16 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">CONJURE</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">12 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">CHARM</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">The Grand Illusion</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">WIZARD — 19 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">W=4, I=1, Z=10, A=1, R=1, D=2 · 6 letters · W+Z power duo</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">A person who practises magic. WIZARD delivers 19 points from just 6 tiles — 3.2 points per tile, exceptional efficiency. The Z=10 and W=4 combine for 14 points alone, with common I, A, R, D as supporting cast.</p>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Spells & Sorcery</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🪄 CONJURE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">16 pts · C=3, O=1, N=1, J=8, U=1, R=1, E=1 · Summon by magic</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✨ HEXING</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">17 pts · H=4, E=1, X=8, I=1, N=1, G=2 · Casting a spell</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🧙 WICKED</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">16 pts · W=4, I=1, C=3, K=5, E=1, D=2 · Evil sorcery</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🔮 OCCULT</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 pts · O=1, C=3, C=3, U=1, L=1, T=1 · Hidden mysteries</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Magical Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">POTION</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CHARM</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SPELL</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">VANISH</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">MYSTIC</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Magic Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">WIZARD pairs W+Z brilliantly:</span> Both W=4 and Z=10 are tricky to deploy. WIZARD gives them a natural home with common tiles (I, A, R, D). On a double-word square that's 38 points.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">CONJURE is a J-bingo:</span> At exactly 7 letters, CONJURE delivers J=8 value plus the 50-point bingo bonus (66 total). The letters C, O, N, U, R, E are all common draws.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">HEXING maximises X placement:</span> The -ING suffix attached to HEX gives X=8 a natural ending. At 17 points from 6 tiles (2.8 pts/tile), this outperforms many longer words.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Magic words are <span class="text-white font-medium">power-tile magnets</span>. WIZARD (W+Z), HEXING (H+X), CONJURE (J) — each deploys a high-value tile alongside common letters. Memorise these for racks containing Z, X, J, or W with standard vowels and consonants.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/best-z-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best Z Words in Scrabble</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/best-x-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best X Words in Scrabble</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-mythology/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Mythology</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid magic word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
